==English==

===Etymology===
From a modern frequentative form of {{term|draw|lang=en}}, equivalent to {{suffix|draw|le}}. Compare {{l|en|draggle}}. Compare also {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|dralen||to drag out, delay, linger, tarry, dawdle|lang=nl}}, Old Danish {{term|dravle||to linger, loiter|lang=da}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|dralla||to loiter, linger|lang=is}}.

